qas.question: How many years ago was Tennessee first inhabited by humans?
What time period corresponds with the Mississippian cultural phase in early Tennessee history?
Which Native American people are the first group to inhabit Tennessee that we know by name?
What do archaeologists call the cultural phase of the inhabitants of Tennessee between 1000 BC and 1000 AD?

context: The area now known as Tennessee was first inhabited by Paleo-Indians nearly <a0_0>12,000<a0_0/> years ago. The names of the cultural groups that inhabited the area between first settlement and the time of European contact are unknown, but several distinct cultural phases have been named by archaeologists, including Archaic (8000–1000 BC), <a3_0>Woodland<a3_0/> (1000 BC–1000 AD), and Mississippian (<a1_0>1000–1600 AD<a1_0/>), whose chiefdoms were the cultural predecessors of the <a2_0>Muscogee<a2_0/> people who inhabited the Tennessee River Valley before Cherokee migration into the river's headwaters.
